Key Takeaways

One of the most important lessons learned was the value of patience and a structured approach to troubleshooting.
Effective troubleshooting requires reviewing configurations carefully, validating user and role assignments, allowing sufficient time for synchronisation and policy propagation, and retesting before implementing additional changes.
I also gained a deeper appreciation for the importance of testing security controls with a limited user group before deploying them across an entire organisation.


